---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---
<DocsLayout
	slug="workflows/dependabot-pr-merge"
	description="The Dependabot PR merge workflow — find already-green dependency-update PRs, assess triviality, and enable auto-merge on the safe ones."
>
	<p>
		Dependabot PR merge is the proactive companion to
		<a href="/docs/workflows/dependabot-ci-fix">Dependabot CI fix</a>. That one
		repairs a dependency-update PR whose CI went <em>red</em>; this one handles
		the PRs that are already <em>green</em> and need no fix — it reads the diff,
		decides whether the bump is trivial, and enables GitHub auto-merge (squash)
		so the safe ones land without a human in the loop.
	</p>

	<div class="docs-callout tip">
		<div class="docs-callout-body">
			<strong>Permission profile:</strong> <code>repo-write</code> — needed only
			for the <code>github_enable_auto_merge</code> tool. It never pushes code
			and never merges directly: enabling auto-merge lets GitHub merge the PR
			once its required checks pass, and GitHub refuses on a red or still-running
			PR — that is the green gate.
		</div>
	</div>

	<h2>Pipeline</h2>

	<div class="workflow-diagram">
		<svg viewBox="0 0 320 80" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
			<rect x="95" y="12" width="130" height="56" rx="8" fill="var(--bg-card)" stroke="var(--diag-line)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
			<text x="160" y="37" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--text)" font-size="11" font-family="Inter">Assess</text>
			<text x="160" y="52" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--diag-grey)" font-size="8" font-family="JetBrains Mono">trivial? → auto-merge</text>
		</svg>
	</div>

	<h2>What it does</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>Inspects each PR through the <code>github_list_pull_request_files</code> tool (changed files + line counts) — no repository checkout is needed — and deliberately skips lockfile diffs, only pulling the full <code>github_get_pull_request_diff</code> for a small non-lockfile source change (reading whole lockfile diffs in scan mode used to overflow the model's context window)</li>
		<li>Classifies the change conservatively: only lockfile / manifest bumps, GitHub Actions tag/SHA bumps, type-only or mechanical edits count as <strong>trivial</strong>; anything touching runtime logic, anything security-sensitive, and major-version bumps are <strong>functional</strong></li>
		<li>If trivial, enables GitHub auto-merge (squash) so the PR merges once its checks pass; otherwise it comments and leaves the PR for a human</li>
		<li>When in doubt, it does not auto-merge</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="docs-callout note">
		<div class="docs-callout-body">
			Auto-merge needs "Allow auto-merge" enabled on the repository and at least
			one required status check. If it isn't available, the workflow comments
			that the update looks trivial and asks a maintainer to merge.
		</div>
	</div>

	<h2>Triggers</h2>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>GitHub webhook:</strong> a <code>check_suite.completed</code> event with a <code>success</code> conclusion on a dependency-update PR (surfaced internally as <code>pr.checks_passed</code>). The connector pre-filters to Dependabot / Renovate — by the head commit author or the <code>dependabot/</code> / <code>renovate/</code> branch prefix — so ordinary green PRs fire nothing. The router routes it deterministically to this workflow. Requires the GitHub App to subscribe to <strong>Check suite</strong> events (Checks: read).</li>
		<li><strong>Cron sweep:</strong> a scheduled scan (<code>mode: scan</code>) sweeps every managed repo for open Dependabot / Renovate PRs and assesses each. Unlike the review scan, it runs <em>alongside</em> webhooks — a safety net that catches PRs which went green before boot or during a missed delivery. Enabling auto-merge is idempotent, so the overlap is harmless.</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="docs-next">
		<a href="/docs/workflows/dependabot-ci-fix" class="prev">
			<span class="label">&larr; Prev</span>
			<span class="title">Dependabot CI fix</span>
		</a>
		<a href="/docs/workflows/repo-health" class="next">
			<span class="label">Next &rarr;</span>
			<span class="title">Repo health</span>
		</a>
	</div>
</DocsLayout>

<style is:global>
	.workflow-diagram {
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
		padding: 1.25rem;
		background: var(--bg-card);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 10px;
		overflow-x: auto;
	}

	.workflow-diagram svg {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 320px;
		height: auto;
		display: block;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}
</style>
